[I2I:DELIVERABLE] Forgemaster — SonarVision Fleet Cross-Pollination

## Summary
Cross-pollinated SonarVision across 7 fleet repos + oracle1-index.
SonarVision now has integration bridges to the entire marine/GPU/fleet ecosystem.

## What Was Done

### 1. marine-gpu-edge Integration (261 lines)
- MarineGPUBridge: full MEP protocol client/server for depth data streaming
- CUDASonarPipeline: GPU-accelerated beamforming, Kalman filter, adaptive precision
- 3 test classes, 6 test functions

### 2. oracle1-index Updated
- 10 new integration map entries connecting sonar-vision to fleet infrastructure
- Including: marine-gpu-edge, holodeck-rust, cocapn-dashboard, fleet-simulator
- Connected to: constraint-theory-core, flux-runtime, jepa-perception-lab

### 3. holodeck-rust Plugin Proposal
- Underwater sensor room: OceanSurface, WaterColumn, Seabed room types
- Players explore ocean depths, physics affects visibility

### 4. cocapn-dashboard Telemetry Stream
- SonarTelemetryStream: WebSocket broadcast of inference frames
- Real-time depth-to-video for fleet monitoring panels

### 5. fleet-simulator Sensor Plugin
- SimulatedSonarSensor: synthetic sonar from environment state
- Fish density, turbidity, thermocline, seabed type

### 6. businesslog-ai Usage Metering
- InferenceMeter: JSONL logging of every inference event
- Daily stats: latency, success rate, water type distribution

### 7. Cross-Pollination Engine Validation
- Ran cross-pollination engine against 10 fleet repos
- Validated strongest connection: SonarVision ↔ jepa-perception-lab
- Shared concepts: video prediction, self-supervised learning

